1
00:00:19,320 --> 00:00:20,720
Is what you said true, Na?

2
00:00:22,080 --> 00:00:23,740
Why didn't you say so earlier?

3
00:00:30,520 --> 00:00:31,720
Na.

4
00:00:33,760 --> 00:00:35,400
Na, it's Linda.

5
00:00:41,640 --> 00:00:42,760
Why are you here?

6
00:00:43,120 --> 00:00:45,050
Are you here to do business with Na?

7
00:00:53,520 --> 00:00:54,840
Let go.

8
00:00:56,120 --> 00:00:57,180
Take your hand off.

9
00:01:00,920 --> 00:01:01,520
Wear this.

10
00:01:24,680 --> 00:01:25,360
Li Na!

11
00:01:27,840 --> 00:01:28,640
Li Na!

12
00:01:29,039 --> 00:01:30,800
Didn't you tell me to come over?

13
00:01:31,039 --> 00:01:31,920
I'm coming in.

14
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:19,480
Xiaoyuan,

15
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:23,320
come to my office.

16
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:29,180
[Serve]

17
00:02:29,240 --> 00:02:30,840
Manager, what do you need me for?

18
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:32,640
Your bonus for this month is on the table.

19
00:02:32,640 --> 00:02:33,040
Take it.

20
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:34,170
Thank you, Manager.

21
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:37,640
Xiaoyuan,

22
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:42,520
do you know why you get a bonus every month?

23
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:48,440
As long as you are obedient.

24
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:49,000
Manager, please don't do this.

25
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,720
I promise to give you a bonus every month.

26
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:51,520
Manager.

27
00:02:54,040 --> 00:02:55,500
Don't you want your bonus?

28
00:03:07,160 --> 00:03:09,240
Xiaoyuan, are you okay?

29
00:03:10,240 --> 00:03:11,520
I'm fine.

30
00:03:11,880 --> 00:03:13,940
Xiaoyuan, did the manager bully you?

31
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:17,440
We all know what kind of person the manager is.

32
00:03:17,640 --> 00:03:19,360
You're the only single girl in the factory.

33
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:20,360
He definitely...

34
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:22,540
Be careful from now on.

35
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:25,240
By the way.

36
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:26,600
We're going to play mahjong tonight.

37
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:27,800
Do you want to join us?

38
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:29,600
I'll pass.

39
00:03:29,760 --> 00:03:30,560
I don't know how to play mahjong.

40
00:03:30,560 --> 00:03:31,720
She played for the first time yesterday.

41
00:03:31,720 --> 00:03:32,840
And she won over a hundred bucks.

42
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:33,360
Yeah.

43
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,860
It's very simple. I'll teach you.

44
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:39,360
Three of Circles.

45
00:03:47,640 --> 00:03:48,700
One of Characters.

46
00:03:51,160 --> 00:03:52,090
Five of Circles.

47
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:53,810
Five of Characters.

48
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:57,480
Mahjong!

49
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:59,040
Pay up.

50
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:00,400
Whether you know how to play or not,

51
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:01,600
you still have to pay.

52
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:13,440
Hey, Brother Hua. Your turn.

53
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:18,680
Brother Hua spent five years in prison

54
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:19,839
without a taste of women.

55
00:04:19,839 --> 00:04:21,200
Now seeing a chick,

56
00:04:21,640 --> 00:04:23,440
he doesn't even know how to play.

57
00:04:23,560 --> 00:04:25,240
You are quite something now.

58
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:27,240
You have your own factory.

59
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:29,640
Brother Hua, I used to call you Brother Hua.

60
00:04:29,840 --> 00:04:32,040
I still call you Brother Hua now.

61
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:34,440
But you need to change your tune.

62
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:36,280
From now on, call me Lord Wu.

63
00:04:36,280 --> 00:04:37,440
You talk too much.

64
00:04:38,080 --> 00:04:40,240
Figure out your tiles first.

65
00:04:40,960 --> 00:04:44,880
Brother Hua, I'm about to win.

66
00:04:48,840 --> 00:04:52,960
These little tricks don't fool me.

67
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:54,040
Cheating!

68
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:14,440
You were about to win.

69
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:16,640
Hua.

70
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:24,040
Hua.

71
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:25,440
Bite down.

72
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:27,720
Hua.

73
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:34,040
You're still waiting for this tile?

74
00:05:36,440 --> 00:05:38,400
Hua, spare me.

75
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:42,880
Still acting like a boss?

76
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:46,040
Fifth Master.

77
00:05:57,840 --> 00:05:58,880
From that table.

78
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:00,210
Stand still.

79
00:06:05,840 --> 00:06:08,520
Give back the money you cheated her out of.

80
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:13,200
Put it down.

81
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:07,280
I just got so much money back for you.

82
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:09,200
You're so cheap. Still walking?

83
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:10,960
Can't I just take a walk?

84
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:12,560
Let me give you a ride.

85
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:16,420
No need. My boyfriend is picking me up later.

86
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:17,800
You have a boyfriend?

87
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:19,970
Okay, I'm leaving then.

88
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:29,760
Hey.

89
00:07:29,960 --> 00:07:31,290
Your boyfriend is here.

90
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:32,920
Get on.

91
00:07:33,800 --> 00:07:34,960
Boring.

92
00:07:36,280 --> 00:07:38,159
There are really no cars this late.

93
00:07:38,159 --> 00:07:38,960
Take a look.

94
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:40,740
Let me take you.

95
00:07:48,159 --> 00:07:49,000
Hold on tight.

96
00:07:50,360 --> 00:07:51,490
You can hold onto me.

97
00:08:06,440 --> 00:08:07,240
Mom.

98
00:08:07,880 --> 00:08:10,200
Who is that hooligan on the motorcycle?

99
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:12,600
A friend.

100
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:14,660
It was too late, so he brought me back.

101
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:15,800
Where did you go?

102
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:17,560
Playing mahjong.

103
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:20,400
You have the money and time to play mahjong.

104
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:21,960
Why don't you work some overtime?

105
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:23,640
Your younger brother is going to college.

106
00:08:23,640 --> 00:08:26,680
As his older sister, why don't you set a good example?

107
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:29,000
You just fool around outside every day.

108
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:33,000
What did I do to deserve this?

109
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,480
To give birth to a burden like you.

110
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:40,360
Let me tell you.

111
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,240
Last week,

112
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:44,480
Aunt Hong introduced you to the guy from the chain store,

113
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:46,210
Mr. Wang from the supermarket.

114
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:48,440
I think he is pretty good.

115
00:08:48,760 --> 00:08:51,020
I will discuss it with him these few days.

116
00:08:51,600 --> 00:08:53,800
You will marry him next month.

117
00:08:54,640 --> 00:08:55,600
I refuse.

118
00:08:56,480 --> 00:08:57,960
You don't like Mr. Wang.

119
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,920
Did you fall for that hooligan?

120
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:02,360
If you have the guts,

121
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:05,000
leave with that little hoodlum right now.

122
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:06,480
Get out! Just leave!

123
00:09:07,040 --> 00:09:09,040
Get as far away from me as possible!

124
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:12,560
Mom, look.

125
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:21,160
Yuanyuan.

126
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:23,860
We don't have money for your college.

127
00:09:24,400 --> 00:09:25,680
Start working first.

128
00:09:25,880 --> 00:09:28,160
I've asked someone to find you a job.

129
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:30,900
Can I work part-time while going to college?

130
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:32,520
In your dreams.

131
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,360
Let's not talk about it.

132
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:36,600
Mom, stop pressuring my sister.

133
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:39,040
Where do you think your tuition comes from?

134
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:41,880
It's all for you, you little ingrate.

135
00:09:49,680 --> 00:09:50,880
Your name is

136
00:09:50,880 --> 00:09:51,610
Hua Weihong.

137
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:57,480
You are so old-fashioned.

138
00:09:58,400 --> 00:09:59,460
Just being polite.

139
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:11,280
Let's go.

140
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:47,970
How is it? I solved this problem for you, didn't I?

141
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:55,580
But you need to protect yourself from now on.

142
00:10:56,360 --> 00:10:57,690
I'm leaving this place.

143
00:11:00,680 --> 00:11:01,610
You're leaving?

144
00:11:01,880 --> 00:11:02,560
Why?

145
00:11:04,560 --> 00:11:08,040
The incident at the mahjong parlor blew up.

146
00:11:08,920 --> 00:11:11,050
I don't want to confront them just yet.

147
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:18,200
Who exactly are you?

148
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:22,200
Does it matter?

149
00:11:32,920 --> 00:11:35,250
Do you want to try a different kind of life?

150
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:38,680
As long as I can leave this place.

151
00:12:04,240 --> 00:12:05,560
Hello, Officer Lin.

152
00:12:05,680 --> 00:12:06,880
My name is Zhang Yang.

153
00:12:08,640 --> 00:12:09,560
Please come in.

154
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:35,340
One victim has obvious ligature marks on their limbs and neck.

155
00:12:36,440 --> 00:12:38,440
This is consistent with death by mechanical asphyxiation.

156
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:40,040
They suffered abuse before death.

157
00:12:40,040 --> 00:12:42,840
It was likely from torture during interrogation.

158
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:57,420
The other victim was likely sexually assaulted before death.

159
00:12:58,080 --> 00:13:00,200
The cause of death was head trauma.
